    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> Synchronizing the releases of all currently supported mods together with the engine isn't a trivial matter though and probably will lead to some player base fragmentation. On the other hand, very actively developed mods don't have to wait for another release cycle to do balancing adjustments etc.\r\n\r\nThis is now covered by #12554, and the centralized database of mods is covered by https://github.com/OpenRA/OpenRA-Resources/issues/204."
